{"article_id":"eFJS0y3NZn8GIPyP","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Republicans are on the verge","depth":10},{"id":1,"text":"of achieving one of biggest policy goals of the past decade :","depth":10},{"id":2,"text":"unraveling the Affordable Care Act .","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"The Tax Cuts and Jobs Act ,","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"as being considered in the US Senate ,","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"repeals Obamacare ' s individual mandate .","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"That change ,","depth":11},{"id":7,"text":"according to the Congressional Budget Office ,","depth":11},{"id":8,"text":"would cut $ 338 billion over 10 years from Medicaid and insurance subsidies","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"and lead to 13 million fewer people","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"having health coverage .","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"That will ,","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"according to the best evidence","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"we have ,","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"lead to an increase in preventable deaths on the order of 15,600 people per year .","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"It will do more than that , though .","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"It will completely destabilize the market for individual health insurance .","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"The individual mandate serves a critically important function for people","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"buying health insurance outside of an employer .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"It makes sure","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"that young and healthy people with low health expenses buy insurance ,","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"which lowers premiums for everyone else .","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"That ensures that people with chronic health conditions","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"who don ' t get insurance from work","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"can buy coverage at an even barely reasonable price .","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"Without the mandate , the individual market could easily collapse into what ' s known as a \" death spiral , \"","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"in which healthy people flee the individual health insurance market en masse ,","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"leaving the remaining customers to just be less healthy or older people ,","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"who ' d then face huge premiums .","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"They ' d get some help from Obamacare ' s insurance subsidies ,","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"which would remain","depth":13},{"id":31,"text":"and cap premiums as a share of income for low- and middle-income people .","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"But even that might not be enough","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"to make the plans affordable .","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"And","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"if enough people quit ,","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"then insurers could stop offering plans in some areas altogether .","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"Some of the healthy and younger people , in turn , would then grow older and sicker .","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"Some would get potentially fatal illnesses ,","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"and","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"without insurance","depth":13},{"id":41,"text":"they wouldn ' t be able to recover .","depth":13},{"id":42,"text":"That ' s where that 15,600 deaths figure becomes relevant .","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"This is Obamacare repeal lite ,","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"and it ' s a serious threat to the safety net","depth":6},{"id":45,"text":"Republicans like to argue","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"that repealing the mandate doesn ' t take health coverage away from anyone .","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"It just lets people choose !","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"Medicaid expansion and insurance subsidies would remain for anyone","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"who wants them .","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"Then-Sen. Barack Obama unwittingly laid the groundwork for this argument in 2007 and 2008 ,","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"when he opposed the mandate in debates with Hillary Clinton","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"and insisted","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"that universal coverage was possible without it .","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"And , indeed , some health care analysts have argued","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"you can create other incentives","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"to ensure","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"healthy people still sign up .","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"Paul Starr , a medical sociologist at Princeton , has proposed","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"barring people","depth":13},{"id":60,"text":"who decline health coverage","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"from government health subsidies for five years ;","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"people would have a choice ,","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"but the choice would have huge negative consequences .","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"Republicans in Congress have proposed","depth":13},{"id":65,"text":"replacing the mandate with a surcharge","depth":14},{"id":66,"text":"you ' d pay","depth":15},{"id":67,"text":"upon returning to health insurance .","depth":15},{"id":68,"text":"Here ' s the thing , though :","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"If you replaced the mandate with something","depth":15},{"id":70,"text":"that actually worked ,","depth":16},{"id":71,"text":"that actually succeeded at getting as many or more people to sign up for coverage ,","depth":16},{"id":72,"text":"the CBO would score that as not saving money , perhaps even as costing money .","depth":14},{"id":73,"text":"Repealing the mandate saves money","depth":14},{"id":74,"text":"by reducing health coverage .","depth":14},{"id":75,"text":"Less health coverage means less Medicaid and insurance subsidy spending by the federal government .","depth":13},{"id":76,"text":"If you replace the mandate with something effective ,","depth":14},{"id":77,"text":"coverage levels stay the same ,","depth":14},{"id":78,"text":"no money is saved ,","depth":14},{"id":79,"text":"and the mandate can ' t be repealed","depth":15},{"id":80,"text":"to pay for tax cuts .","depth":15},{"id":81,"text":"Put another way :","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"Either the Senate tax bill kicks millions of people off insurance","depth":13},{"id":83,"text":"or it costs $ 338 billion more","depth":14},{"id":84,"text":"than its supporters say","depth":15},{"id":85,"text":"it does .","depth":15},{"id":86,"text":"Reasonable people can argue about whether the 13 million figure is too high","depth":15},{"id":87,"text":"( or too low ) .","depth":15},{"id":88,"text":"But we don ' t need to know the exact magnitude","depth":15},{"id":89,"text":"to know","depth":16},{"id":90,"text":"that repealing the mandate means millions fewer people with health insurance ,","depth":17},{"id":91,"text":"and risks far higher premiums for those","depth":18},{"id":92,"text":"still getting health insurance .","depth":18},{"id":93,"text":"This , for most Americans , is the most significant change in this bill .","depth":13},{"id":94,"text":"That ' s especially true","depth":14},{"id":95,"text":"if the individual tax cut changes are ,","depth":16},{"id":96,"text":"as Republicans are insisting ,","depth":16},{"id":97,"text":"meant to be permanent .","depth":15},{"id":98,"text":"( In the bill","depth":17},{"id":99,"text":"as written ,","depth":17},{"id":100,"text":"they expire at the end of 2025 ,","depth":16},{"id":101,"text":"resulting in an across-the-board tax increase on individuals ,","depth":15},{"id":102,"text":"but Republicans say","depth":15},{"id":103,"text":"they ' d intervene","depth":16},{"id":104,"text":"to prevent that from happening . )","depth":16},{"id":105,"text":"For the middle class , the tax cuts in this bill are minimal .","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"Millions of people would even see tax hikes .","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"All of those changes pale in comparison to losing your health insurance ,","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"because you didn ' t have the individual mandate","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"to nudge you to buy .","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"They pale compared to seeing your premiums double or triple","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"because the individual market has gone into a death spiral .","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"The most acute changes","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"this bill will make in Americans ' lives","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"have to do with health care , not taxes .","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"And the changes are all profoundly negative .","depth":8},{"id":116,"text":"At this point , Republicans ' repeated efforts","depth":7},{"id":117,"text":"to repeal Obamacare","depth":7},{"id":118,"text":"are something of a joke among liberals and Democrats .","depth":6},{"id":119,"text":"First Paul Ryan failed to push something through the House in March .","depth":7},{"id":120,"text":"Then he got his act together ,","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"passed something ,","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"and the Senate failed to pass anything , not even \" skinny repeal. \"","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"Then there was a boomlet for the Graham-Cassidy proposal in September ,","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"which quickly petered out","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"and died .","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"Each time , in the Senate , the proposals were defeated by a triad of Republican senators :","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"moderates Susan Collins and Lisa Murkowski , and John McCain ,","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"who seems to just like stirring the pot .","depth":12},{"id":129,"text":"It was the legislative equivalent of the Simpsons scene","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"where Sideshow Bob steps on rakes for , like , 30 straight seconds .","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"Liberals shouldn ' t be laughing anymore .","depth":6},{"id":132,"text":"Now even Collins appears on board with the attempt","depth":7},{"id":133,"text":"to repeal the individual mandate in the context of tax reform .","depth":7},{"id":134,"text":"So is Bob Corker of Tennessee , another potential defector .","depth":6},{"id":135,"text":"Barring some sudden changes ,","depth":7},{"id":136,"text":"this is going to pass the US Senate","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"and quite likely become law .","depth":8},{"id":138,"text":"There ' s a chance , of course , that in conference committee the individual mandate repeal will be stripped out .","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"It wasn ' t in the bill","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"that passed the House , after all .","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"But","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"if Susan Collins won ' t stand up","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"to defend the mandate ,","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"does anyone really think","depth":11},{"id":145,"text":"enough members of the House will ?","depth":11},{"id":146,"text":"And with the mandate repeal raising $ 338 billion","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"to pay for tax cuts","depth":10},{"id":148,"text":"Republicans desperately want ,","depth":10},{"id":149,"text":"do we really think","depth":9},{"id":150,"text":"they ' d part with it easily ?","depth":9},{"id":151,"text":"Republicans really are on the verge","depth":5},{"id":152,"text":"of repealing a significant part of Obamacare ,","depth":5},{"id":153,"text":"of substantially growing the ranks of the uninsured","depth":5},{"id":154,"text":"and perhaps irrevocably damaging the health insurance market .","depth":5},{"id":155,"text":"They are dismantling one of the most important progressive achievements since the Great Society .","depth":4},{"id":156,"text":"They aren ' t just cutting tax cuts for rich people .","depth":5},{"id":157,"text":"They ' re reshaping the health care safety net in ways","depth":6},{"id":158,"text":"that will reverberate for years","depth":7},{"id":159,"text":"if they succeed .","depth":7},{"id":160,"text":"Are you an Obamacare enrollee interested in what happens next ?","depth":2},{"id":161,"text":"Join our Facebook community for conversation and updates .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":323,"left":321,"right":322,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":321,"lef